<div class="d1">
    <h2>Panels</h2>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="col-md-6 p-t-34">
            <div class="bty-panel">
                <div>
                    <span>Panel Title</span>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p>It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when
                        looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal
                        distribution of letters, as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like
                        readable English.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h5>bty-panel</h5>
            <textarea class="form-control" name="" id="" cols="30" rows="5" readonly>
                .bty-panel {
    display: block;
    position: relative;
    background-color: #afbbc126;
}
                .bty-panel > div:first-child{
    padding: .625rem 0;
    color: #ffffff;
    background-color: #afbbc1;
    cursor: default;
    vertical-align: middle;
    z-index: 2;
    height: 40px;
    box-shadow: -1px 6px 6px -6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
}

.bty-panel > div:first-child span:last-child {
    padding-left: 20px;
    font-size: 20px;
}

.bty-panel > div:last-child {
    padding: 20px;
}
            </textarea>
        </div>

    </div>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h4>With Icon</h4>
        <h5>bty-panel bty-panel-icon</h5>
        <div class="bty-panel bty-panel-icon">
            <div>
                <span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-sliders" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                <span>Panel Title</span>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page when
                    looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal
                    distribution of letters, as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like
                    readable English.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Panel Collapse</h2>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h5>bty-panel-collapse</h5>
        <div class="bty-panel-collapse">
            <div>
                <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapseOne"
                   aria-expanded="true">
                    <span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-chevron-down" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
                    <span class="title">Panel Title</span>
                </a>
            </div>
            <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse in" aria-expanded="true" style="">
                <div class="content">
                    <p>It is a long established fact that a reader will be distracted by the readable content of a page
                        when looking at its layout. The point of using Lorem Ipsum is that it has a more-or-less normal
                        distribution of letters, as opposed to using 'Content here, content here', making it look like
                        readable English.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <h2>Colors</h2>
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
            <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Color name</th>
                <th>Class</th>
                <th>Color</th>
            </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            <tr>
                <td>DeepSkyBlue </td>
                <td>bty-panel-cl-deepskyblue</td>
                <td style="background-color: DeepSkyBlue;"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Tomato</td>
                <td>bty-panel-cl-tomato</td>
                <td style="background-color: Tomato;"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Blue</td>
                <td>bty-panel-cl-blue</td>
                <td style="background-color: #499bc7;"></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>Orange</td>
                <td>bty-panel-cl-Orange</td>
                <td style="background-color: Orange;"></td>
            </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

    </div>

</div>